00:00:07.354 --> 00:00:09.756 position:38% line:89% align:start
AD 2619

00:00:09.790 --> 00:00:12.025 position:7% line:83% align:start
(SHICHISEI) <i>Human disease has</i>
 <i>many causes.</i>

00:00:13.026 --> 00:00:18.364 position:19% line:77% align:start
 <i>Of course, as you all</i>
 <i>know, there are microbes such</i>
 <i>as bacteria and viruses.</i>

00:00:19.031 --> 00:00:20.366 position:16% line:89% align:start
(JOSEPH) <i>Not to mention,</i>

00:00:21.133 --> 00:00:21.901 position:24% line:89% align:start
...love, as well.

00:00:24.036 --> 00:00:25.004 position:24% line:89% align:start
As I was saying...

00:00:26.504 --> 00:00:30.875 position:7% line:77% align:start
Bacteria can be parasitic in
nature, residing inside host
organisms.

00:00:31.209 --> 00:00:37.082 position:5% line:77% align:start
And, as living things, they are
capable of migrating, dividing,
and multiplying.

00:00:38.116 --> 00:00:42.087 position:5% line:83% align:start
Viruses, however, have no way to
reproduce autonomously.

00:00:42.519 --> 00:00:46.023 position:5% line:83% align:start
Instead, they have to parasitize
another organism's cells.

00:00:47.024 --> 00:00:51.528 position:10% line:83% align:start
They must use host cells in
order to replicate themselves...

00:00:51.562 --> 00:00:54.131 position:5% line:83% align:start
...and that often destroys those
cells in the process.

00:00:56.200 --> 00:01:02.739 position:10% line:71% align:start
 <i>In other cases, viruses from</i>
 <i>different animals can mutate </i>
 <i>suddenly and then infect humans</i>
 <i>as well.</i>

00:01:06.909 --> 00:01:13.582 position:19% line:71% align:start
 <i>In situations such as</i>
 <i>those, the virus can destroy</i>
 <i>its new, unfamiliar home, the</i>
 <i>human cell.</i>

00:01:14.583 --> 00:01:18.587 position:5% line:77% align:start
 <i>The immune system of the human </i>
 <i>host may then respond</i>
 <i>disproportionately...</i>

00:01:19.587 --> 00:01:22.090 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>...resulting in the emergence of</i>
 <i>illness.</i>

00:01:27.661 --> 00:01:33.533 position:5% line:71% align:start
There you have it. All of these
are the basic mechanisms of
infectious diseases in human
beings.

00:01:35.568 --> 00:01:37.771 position:5% line:83% align:start
And now, the reason that you're
all here.

00:01:50.616 --> 00:01:52.951 position:5% line:89% align:start
 <i>This is the Alien Engine Virus.</i>

00:01:53.253 --> 00:01:56.789 position:16% line:83% align:start
It's a new form of virus
that could wipe out humanity...

00:01:57.990 --> 00:02:01.193 position:5% line:83% align:start
...since the mortality rate is
one hundred percent...

00:02:02.593 --> 00:02:04.896 position:5% line:83% align:start
Its existence has not yet been
made public.

00:02:08.266 --> 00:02:15.472 position:7% line:71% align:start
 <i>Even a new virus will usually</i>
 <i>have a closely related strain</i>
 <i>that can be found residing in</i>
 <i>another plant or animal host.</i>

00:02:16.274 --> 00:02:20.644 position:16% line:77% align:start
 <i>But the Alien Engine, or</i>
 <i>A.E., Virus is a different</i>
 <i>story.</i>

00:02:22.145 --> 00:02:24.480 position:24% line:89% align:start
Heh. Interesting.

00:02:26.817 --> 00:02:27.818 position:24% line:89% align:start
(SHICHISEI) <i>May I?</i>

00:02:30.020 --> 00:02:35.558 position:5% line:71% align:start
 <i>It appeared suddenly forty-two </i>
 <i>years ago. Then twenty years</i>
 <i>ago, it began multiplying</i>
 <i>rapidly.</i>

00:02:35.591 --> 00:02:35.991 position:35% line:89% align:start
 <i>Meaning...</i>

00:02:36.826 --> 00:02:38.493 position:10% line:83% align:start
that it's all the captain's
fault!

00:02:38.994 --> 00:02:40.896 position:35% line:89% align:start
[growling]

00:02:41.130 --> 00:02:43.898 position:5% line:89% align:start
Better watch it, senile Ruskie.

00:02:44.200 --> 00:02:45.667 position:35% line:89% align:start
[growling]

00:02:46.135 --> 00:02:46.168 position:33% line:89% align:start
[chuckling]

00:02:46.835 --> 00:02:48.837 position:10% line:89% align:start
Aw, scolded by a little girl

00:02:48.870 --> 00:02:52.907 position:7% line:83% align:start
who's about the same age as my
very own daughter. [laugh]

00:02:52.941 --> 00:02:54.809 position:7% line:89% align:start
I'm shaking in my boots here!

00:02:55.176 --> 00:02:55.844 position:24% line:89% align:start
(SHICHISEI) <i>Ahem!</i>

00:02:56.677 --> 00:02:57.511 position:38% line:89% align:start
 <i>Please.</i>

00:02:58.745 --> 00:03:00.881 position:7% line:83% align:start
 <i>Since we cannot cultivate the</i>
 <i>virus in a lab, </i>

00:03:02.683 --> 00:03:06.286 position:5% line:77% align:start
 <i>we need an abundance of samples</i>
 <i>from its source if we hope to be</i>
 <i>able to create a vaccine.</i>

00:03:07.020 --> 00:03:10.523 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>And that's why...we'll be</i>
 <i>sending a team to Mars.</i>

00:03:12.859 --> 00:03:15.862 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>Humanity's survival is hanging </i>
 <i>in the balance.</i>

00:04:47.380 --> 00:04:52.384 position:33% line:5% align:start
02 DEPARTURE

00:05:01.793 --> 00:05:06.864 position:13% line:89% align:start
(SHOKICHI) <i>Uh...</i> [coughing]

00:05:06.898 --> 00:05:08.333 position:38% line:89% align:start
AD 2620

00:05:08.866 --> 00:05:10.667 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>Team, this is your captain,</i>
 <i>Komachi, speaking.</i>

00:05:12.502 --> 00:05:17.507 position:7% line:77% align:start
Our vessel, the Annex 1, has
exited Earth's atmosphere and
is heading to Mars on autopilot.

00:05:17.541 --> 00:05:22.645 position:16% line:71% align:start
Till we land on Mars in
thirty-nine days, the
residential quarters will be
your home.

00:05:22.980 --> 00:05:26.782 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>The ship is outfitted with </i>
 <i>artificial gravity, but still...</i>

00:05:26.816 --> 00:05:27.817 position:24% line:89% align:start
Hey, how cool!...

00:05:29.585 --> 00:05:30.753 position:13% line:77% align:start
 <i>...daily training will be </i>
 <i>critical to prevent your muscles</i>
 <i>from  atrophying.</i>

00:05:31.587 --> 00:05:32.088 position:5% line:83% align:start
...no way! How'd they pull that
off?

00:05:33.389 --> 00:05:35.992 position:7% line:83% align:start
 <i>As a reminder, the officers' </i>
 <i>area is off-limits.</i>

00:05:36.459 --> 00:05:39.661 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>But if you encounter problems, </i>
 <i>use the comm to contact us.</i>

00:05:39.928 --> 00:05:42.097 position:10% line:89% align:start
[scoffs] Talk about stuffy.

00:05:44.632 --> 00:05:50.738 position:16% line:71% align:start
 <i>Also, some the officers</i>
 <i>on board are single, including</i>
 <i>Michelle, Joseph, and, yours</i>
 <i>truly!</i> [chuckling]

00:05:50.771 --> 00:05:51.172 position:41% line:89% align:start
Wha-?

00:05:51.839 --> 00:05:53.108 position:21% line:89% align:start
 <i>Don't hold back now!</i>

00:05:54.409 --> 00:05:56.243 position:13% line:77% align:start
Wow! Well, this guy sure
doesn't seem too worried, does
he?

00:05:56.478 --> 00:05:58.679 position:19% line:89% align:start
[scoffs] Not at all...

00:06:00.014 --> 00:06:05.085 position:7% line:83% align:start
[chuckle and sigh] And now, we
wait.

00:06:05.119 --> 00:06:09.088 position:7% line:77% align:start
[chuckle] All right guys, you
can get going and explore the
place.

00:06:09.122 --> 00:06:10.323 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:06:10.356 --> 00:06:11.691 position:13% line:89% align:start
 <i>Yeah! Me first! Me first!</i>

00:06:12.025 --> 00:06:13.026 position:30% line:89% align:start
 <i>If you say so!</i>

00:06:13.393 --> 00:06:15.395 position:7% line:89% align:start
 <i>So Kana, what are we gonna do?</i>

00:06:15.428 --> 00:06:16.996 position:21% line:89% align:start
 <i>Find a few good men!</i>

00:06:17.529 --> 00:06:19.465 position:19% line:89% align:start
Oh, um...Hey, Sheila?

00:06:19.499 --> 00:06:20.199 position:38% line:89% align:start
Hmm...?

00:06:20.899 --> 00:06:22.801 position:7% line:89% align:start
You wouldn't by any chance...

00:06:22.834 --> 00:06:24.736 position:10% line:89% align:start
like the captain, would you?

00:06:25.771 --> 00:06:27.839 position:35% line:89% align:start
[coughing]

00:06:28.140 --> 00:06:30.242 position:13% line:89% align:start
It's true....I thought so.

00:06:32.943 --> 00:06:34.912 position:7% line:83% align:start
The day before the surgery I
was...

00:06:36.147 --> 00:06:36.914 position:27% line:89% align:start
...terrified...

00:06:37.948 --> 00:06:38.816 position:24% line:89% align:start
It was all just...

00:06:39.984 --> 00:06:42.386 position:7% line:83% align:start
 <i>...too much, so I skipped out</i>
 <i>on training.</i>

00:06:50.894 --> 00:06:54.230 position:5% line:83% align:start
Have you...come here to take me
back?

00:06:55.799 --> 00:06:56.366 position:33% line:89% align:start
Not at all.

00:06:57.534 --> 00:06:59.235 position:16% line:89% align:start
I come here to cry, too.

00:07:00.669 --> 00:07:05.074 position:7% line:77% align:start
It's my secret sobbing spot.
I come out here from time to
time...

00:07:06.008 --> 00:07:07.910 position:7% line:83% align:start
...when I need to get out my
frustrations.

00:07:09.811 --> 00:07:12.814 position:7% line:83% align:start
Otherwise, to be honest, I'd
probably fall apart.

00:07:13.382 --> 00:07:14.183 position:35% line:89% align:start
[slurping]

00:07:15.417 --> 00:07:16.250 position:38% line:89% align:start
[inhale]

00:07:19.420 --> 00:07:20.755 position:5% line:89% align:start
(EVA) <i>Are you gonna tell him....</i>

00:07:21.823 --> 00:07:22.490 position:50% line:89% align:start
...how you feel?

00:07:23.690 --> 00:07:26.494 position:5% line:83% align:start
Course not! I mean, there's just
no way we'd ever work out!

00:07:27.127 --> 00:07:29.062 position:10% line:83% align:start
That's true. He is twice your
age.

00:07:29.096 --> 00:07:30.330 position:10% line:89% align:start
No, that's not what I mean!

00:07:30.597 --> 00:07:31.765 position:35% line:89% align:start
[chuckle]

00:07:32.699 --> 00:07:36.303 position:10% line:83% align:start
Oh, uh... Well, I...I didn't
mean that...

00:07:36.970 --> 00:07:40.440 position:10% line:83% align:start
Oh, look! The shower room!
Let's check out the facilities!

00:07:42.442 --> 00:07:46.779 position:35% line:89% align:start
[humming]

00:07:49.582 --> 00:07:50.449 position:44% line:89% align:start
Uh!

00:07:50.849 --> 00:07:53.017 position:5% line:89% align:start
Oh! I'm sorry! We didn't know-!

00:07:53.852 --> 00:07:57.456 position:7% line:83% align:start
It isn't a problem at all. I
guess I forgot to lock the door.

00:07:57.856 --> 00:08:07.298 position:30% line:89% align:start
[loud exhales]

00:08:11.268 --> 00:08:12.236 position:35% line:89% align:start
[chuckle]

00:08:16.039 --> 00:08:17.907 position:7% line:89% align:start
Your name's Sheila, isn't it?

00:08:18.408 --> 00:08:19.842 position:30% line:89% align:start
Uh...Yeah....

00:08:21.278 --> 00:08:23.380 position:19% line:89% align:start
Tell him how you feel.

00:08:23.413 --> 00:08:24.180 position:38% line:89% align:start
Huh...?!

00:08:25.248 --> 00:08:27.884 position:5% line:83% align:start
Women are meant to fall in love,
whatever may come.

00:08:28.084 --> 00:08:29.485 position:35% line:89% align:start
[gasping]

00:08:30.486 --> 00:08:33.289 position:5% line:83% align:start
Older men...that's not really my
thing, though.

00:08:34.157 --> 00:08:39.161 position:10% line:83% align:start
Not in this lifetime. Not a
chance! [laughing]

00:08:39.928 --> 00:08:43.365 position:24% line:77% align:start
I guess she's Miss
 <i>Posi</i> - <i>titty-</i> ty... Or
something...

00:08:43.398 --> 00:08:44.332 position:38% line:89% align:start
Huh...?!

00:08:53.974 --> 00:08:55.843 position:27% line:89% align:start
20 Days to Mars

00:08:56.644 --> 00:08:57.311 position:38% line:89% align:start
[thump]

00:08:57.611 --> 00:08:59.012 position:38% line:89% align:start
[slurp]

00:09:04.652 --> 00:09:05.519 position:38% line:89% align:start
[grunt]

00:09:07.053 --> 00:09:11.924 position:33% line:89% align:start
[thud] Owww!

00:09:14.661 --> 00:09:15.861 position:44% line:89% align:start
See?

00:09:16.828 --> 00:09:17.564 position:5% line:83% align:start
Of course it's the only thing
he's good at...

00:09:18.363 --> 00:09:20.432 position:13% line:83% align:start
Only thing since we were all
kids

00:09:20.465 --> 00:09:21.533 position:38% line:89% align:start
Uh-huh!

00:09:22.968 --> 00:09:25.671 position:5% line:77% align:start
Yeah, well I don't care if it's
the only thing, it still
freakin hurts!

00:09:25.703 --> 00:09:28.172 position:16% line:83% align:start
Hey, I'm good at lots of
thing!

00:09:28.207 --> 00:09:31.042 position:5% line:5% align:start
(JASON) <i>Say that one more time,</i>
 <i>bastard!</i>

00:09:31.409 --> 00:09:31.876 position:35% line:89% align:start
[growling]

00:09:33.344 --> 00:09:34.879 position:5% line:83% align:start
(AKARI) <i>That blonde guy's in the</i>
 <i>same  squad as you are, right?</i>

00:09:35.213 --> 00:09:36.647 position:13% line:89% align:start
(MARCOS) <i>Man, he's pissed.</i>

00:09:36.681 --> 00:09:37.949 position:5% line:89% align:start
(SHEILA) <i>Shouldn't we stop him?</i>

00:09:37.982 --> 00:09:39.183 position:33% line:89% align:start
[growling]

00:09:39.217 --> 00:09:40.117 position:27% line:89% align:start
Let's see, so...

00:09:41.051 --> 00:09:42.986 position:5% line:83% align:start
